, they were" b'all from kafan.' b'' b'the secretary of the party organization is named najaf, najaf rzayev. he was' b"there when everything started. it must have been him because i didn't" b'recognize anyone else in the crowd whom i knew besides him. all the more since' b'i told him, "listen, you do something, because you know me." he turned away' b"and went toward the bedroom, where marina was. well you couldn't see marina" b"anyway. there was such a noisy confusion of people that you couldn't make out" b'anyone. all of it flew right out of my head, and then gradually i became' b'myself again, at the city party committee there were military people' b'there. i told them what went on, and they wrote it all down. i told them his' b'name. on march the secretary of our first trust party organization, the one' b'we\'re part of, came to see us, his name is najaf rzayev. i tell mamma, "if' b"he's here despite the fact that i gave his name, it means that either his" b"alibi has been confirmed or, probably, that they think i'm crazy, not" b'responsible for my words." he said, "what did they do to you, how awful,' b'myself, i hid an armenian family." then after some time goes by he comes back' b'again and says something entirely different: "i wasn\'t at home, my family and' b'i went to baku." i said, "marina, what is he saying? he said something totally' b'different before." after that i didn\'t go to see our procurator, our case is' b'being handled by a procurator from voronezh, fedorov by name. fedorov told me' b"that rzayev's case had just gotten to him, and there were so names involved." b'what are they doing with rzayev?' b'did he prove his alibi or not? they just think that since i was hit in the' b"head i can't say anything for sure, whether it was him or not. it will be an" b"insult if he was in our apartment and doesn't have to pay for it, but at the" b'same time' b'' b"i'm afraid to say i'm a hundred percent sure that it was he. because no mat-" b"ter who i name, th